Topics illustrated: outliers in residuals, significance versus fit, effect of sample size on t-statistics. 265 observations, 7 predictors. Dependent variable is the ideal number of children for a married couple. Independent variables are gender, parents' family size, parent dominance, political orientation, and attendance at religious services. Data is from a survey of MBA students in six classes at a medium-size public AACSB-accredited business school in the north central U.S in September, 1990 and again in February, 1998. Any respondent whose replies were incomplete or ambiguous was excluded.
